	name = "recycling notice"
	default_raw_text = "Anything without a resale value, throw into the recycling crushers. Walls and floors, strip the plating off them, cut them up and throw the remains into the crushers. Anything left over goes in the crushers. Keep a good pace, and don't hoard garbage. The faster we clear the collection area the faster we can wreck more vessels."


/obj/item/paper/fluff/awaymissions/piratefleet/shipwrecker/rambling/spacecryptid
	default_raw_text = "Brian says there's been scratches on the outside of the hull. Not the usual scars from space debris and carp bites, he says that he's had to patch up deep gouges in the external airlocks that look more like the claws of an animal. Huge, too - he reckons they gotta have talons about a foot long. Giant monsters that can survive in a total vaccum, and they want to board our ship. Ain't that a nice thought?"

/obj/item/paper/fluff/awaymissions/piratefleet/shipwrecker/rambling/spacecryptid/skeptic
	default_raw_text = "These 'void bugs' are mass hysteria induced by bad drugs. Some of these stim batches haven't been stored properly, stop using the shit if its spoilage indicator is lit up. And stop refilling the needles with other drugs, you dumb bastards!"

/obj/item/paper/fluff/awaymissions/piratefleet/shipwrecker/rambling/spacecryptid/sighting
	default_raw_text = "I think I saw one of those void bugs the crew's been talking about. Heard the external turret activate, go to check on it, and see some kinda bug corpse rolling past the window through hyperspace. It was big, bigger than a person, and covered in purple bug shaped armour. "

/obj/item/paper/fluff/awaymissions/piratefleet/shipwrecker/rambling/treasure
	default_raw_text = "Treasure haul has been good lately. Shot down a bunch of science shuttles, the Marauders buy the equipment and prototypes and we melt the rest down. More lucrative than hitting cargo shuttles, and usually less guarded."

/obj/item/paper/fluff/awaymissions/piratefleet/shipwrecker/rambling/triangle
	default_raw_text = "Everything with a triangle drawn on it is MINE, got it? Don't touch em. I shoot thieves."

